message.content:
1. A woman sitting in front of a TV, watching the inauguration with a worried expression, while drowning herself in excitement.
2. A man standing alone in a dark alley, feeling blamed for everything that has gone wrong.
3. A student sitting at a desk, surrounded by books and notes, looking jaded and tired.
4. A person standing at a crossroads, feeling torn between taking the boring route or the adventurous one.
5. A group of workers in a factory, feeling valued and integral to the operation, despite doing minuscule work.
6. A person sitting on a couch, feeling mellow about a move, while their partner is feeling anxious.
7. A room filled with dust bunnies, making a person feel useless and insignificant.
8. A woman standing alone on a cliff, feeling unsupported and discouraged.
9. A person lying in bed, feeling groggy and guilty for not being productive.
10. A person walking out of a building, feeling relieved and free after quitting a job they hated.
11. A person sitting in a park, feeling agitated and restless for no apparent reason.
12. A person walking on a deserted street, feeling sociable and looking for company.
13. A person sitting on a bench, feeling drained and exhausted, needing to recharge.
14. A person standing in front of a door, feeling reluctant to enter.
15. A person sitting in a garden, feeling hopeful and encouraged after receiving a phone call.
16. A person standing in front of a house, feeling unwelcome and out of place.
17. A person sitting alone, feeling conflicted about self-injury and scars, and how they make others feel.
18. A person walking on a beach, feeling reluctant to enter the water.
19. A person sitting at a table, feeling like the pomegranate seeds are the only thing cutting through the oily dish.
20. A person standing in a field, feeling blessed and at peace, knowing what they want in a partner.
21. A person scrolling through social media, feeling unimpressed and uninterested in most posts.
22. A person sitting with a friend, feeling glad to be able to help others through compassion and listening.
23. A person sitting at a desk, feeling stressed and overwhelmed with upcoming events and tasks.
24. A person sitting alone, feeling needy and vulnerable.
25. A person sitting in a room, feeling bored and hating the feeling.
26. A person sitting with a family member, feeling helpless and unable to help them feel better.
27. A person running through a park, feeling frantic and trying to remember to breathe.
28. A person sitting alone, feeling ungrateful for not having many friends to write about.
29. A person sitting at a table, feeling like a lame wife and not doing enough.
30. A person sitting with a friend, feeling mad and bothered by something that happened the day before.
31. A person standing in a crowd, feeling a sense of community and support for a person on stage.
32. A person standing on a mountaintop, feeling joyful and excited for a new beginning.
33. A person sitting alone, feeling sentimental and reflective about the past.
34. A person holding a baby, feeling like handing them over to someone else because they're so cute.
35. A person sitting on a bike, feeling paranoid and worried about getting a puncture during a race.
36. A person reading an article, feeling empowered and informed about when not to mediate.
37. A person sitting with a partner, feeling submissive and wanting to please them.
38. A person standing in a protest, feeling strongly against violent methods to achieve political goals.
39. A person dancing in a club, feeling carefree and young.
40. A person sitting in a meeting, feeling valuable and appreciated for their input.
41. A person sitting at a desk, feeling uncertain about the structure of a revalidation portfolio.
42. A person sitting in a formal setting, feeling out of place and wanting to be more relaxed.
43. A person standing in a group, feeling disrespected and uncomfortable, despite being nice.
44. A person sitting alone, feeling rushed and confused about what to do next.
45. A person sitting on a bench, feeling discouraged and defeated.
46. A person watching a movie, feeling disturbed and uncomfortable with the gratuitous violence.
47. A person offering a couch or floor to sleep on, feeling caring and supportive.
48. A person sitting alone, feeling melancholy and sad for the characters in a movie with a sad soundtrack.
49. A person trying a new technique, feeling amazed at how quickly they adapt and pick it up.
50. A person standing in a dark room, feeling no joy and overwhelmed by a fearful dread.
